content.xhtml:p: This example shows how to use an Arduino sketch combined with an IEC 61131-3 PLC program. Two variables are shared between the PLC program and the Arduino sketch: SerialMSG and PrintMSG. On the PLC side, SerialMSG is set to be 'this is a string from ladder'. A square wave generator on 'blink_led' connects to PrintMSG, instructing the Arduino sketch to print SerialMSG on the serial port at every rising edge of the 'blink_led'.
